tip.text: My husband recommends the friarielli veg & zucchini alle scapece which are outstanding! Paste with cozze & clam & pasta with monk fish are delicious but baba soaked with rum (dessert) is heavenly!
Dim sum a bit costly at $48-80.Roast chicken w/truffle is quite delicious,stir-fried string bean is good but small portion, beef w/ rice noodle is average, fried bean curd sheet with cheese is tasty.

Newly opened Malaysian restaurant, simple, quite authentic but nothing to die for. Beef redang is good but portion very small, chow kwai teo not bad, morning glory is tasteless, lime drinks too sweet.

location.address: Shop A, UG/F, The L Place, 139 Queen's Road
formattedAddress: Shop A, UG/F, The L Place, 139 Queen's Road

tip.text: Cute little Mexican restaurant in Wanchai, great value at $78 for the lunch set including tea/soda/coffee. We ordered half grilled chicken and wet burritoes which are both tasty, dessert costs extra.

Always love the ramen here, service is quick & friendly. I ordered the spicy one but it is not too spicy which is perfect! The gyoza is great, love the tons of ginger & green onion topping. $200 for 2

We'd fish cakes which has 6 pcs & soft shell crab curry which is very generous but not tasty, beef Thai salad's beef is chewy while only kale is tasty.Thai milk tea is too strong & lime soda is not gd
Had our midnight 'snack' after movie, ordered the appetiser set which has jellly fish, ox tongue, pig stomach, squid, goose intestine plus famous yummy goose noodles & delicious chicken soup!
Our crab cake & kale are delicious, grill chicken is good but need extra salt, the mash potato is yummy but there seems to have water around it then we found out from manager it is broth...
Love the harbour view here, I prefer the corner tables in the private area, nice & cozy. Had caesar salad with prawns at $280, not cheap & small portion but tasty, love their fresh bread w/ yoghurt!
My 5x in 6 wks,1st time for dinner & still find the dishes delicious & tasty,music is slightly loud,Peking duck is yummy with diff sauce for skin, meat only & skin w/ meat.Love their lobster noodle!

location.address: Shop G04, G/F, Man Yee Arcade, Man Yee Building, 68 Des Voeux Road, Central
formattedAddress: Shop G04, G/F, Man Yee Arcade, Man Yee Building, 68 Des Voeux Road, Central

tip.text: Chicken tikka & Singapore fried noodles are good here!

venue.name: The Peak Lookout 太平山餐廳

tip.text: Nice fun environment,very friendly service from our waitress, Miriam. We ordered taco & fried chicken as starters then stone bowl rice & pork belly, very tasty & gd price, w/ 2 glasses of red at $1k/2
Always love the venue esp with the garden, food is avg but best is to order Indian or Asian food such as Singapore Fried Noodle or Chicken Tikka w/ naan. Service is not attentive but cld b improved.
Quite disappointed with the dishes overall, famous roast goose is avg, Yat Lok is still the best. All dishes size had reduced, not very tasty & very few fish in the fish dish. 5 pax/$2,600 no wine...
First time here, ordered 'spring roll' spicy noodles only $51, I like the spicy soup but not so much the 'spring roll'.....

venue.name: Nam Kee h 南記 h

tip.text: Nice decor quiet ambience for Chinese restaurant, harbour view. Tried their beef brisket in soup, pot rice with Chin sausage, tofu, string bean dishes. Taste is authentic, quite good.$300/pax no wine.
Food is good but not exceptional, $485 per pax incl wine/OJ is not too bad these days. Salmon appetizer is mediocre, french onion soup is ok, Duck thigh was nice & crispy, like the warm cheesecake.

location.address: 3A, 3/F, Shun Fat Bldg, 72-76 Queen's Rd E
formattedAddress: 3A, 3/F, Shun Fat Bldg, 72-76 Queen's Rd E

tip.text: Just reopened few days ago under new mgmt co, same chef, venue is slightly bigger, more spacious.Food is just as good, same dishes. We had squid, Hainan chicken rice, goose intestine, fried fish,crab!

venue.name: Old Bazaar Kitchen 老巴剎廚房

tip.text: New Indonesian restaurant with a modern yet nostalgic & comfy decor.Love the food, authentic but with a twist, ordered nasi goreng, chicken wings, cabbage salad, mojitos & all very tasty!will be back!

2nd visit in 2 weeks,jam pack, food is still very good esp tasted by my Shanghainese friend.This time we tried beef cheek which is very tender, e-fu noodles, spicy dumpling, smoke rolls all excellent!

location.address: Shop G04, G/F, Man Yee Arcade, Man Yee Building, 68 Des Voeux Road, Central
formattedAddress: Shop G04, G/F, Man Yee Arcade, Man Yee Building, 68 Des Voeux Road, Central

tip.text: 2nd time here in 20 yrs, famous HK institution but very disappointed, dim sum & BBQ pork are mediocre, beef fried noodles is ok but price is very expensive, same as China Tang & more!Won't be back!

venue.name: Luk Yu Tea House (陸羽茶室)

tip.text: A very hard to book yakitori restaurant in Central, limited seating but have private room. The food is delicious & unusual,skewers of every chicken part you could think of including liver, bump, comb!
Love the decor & environment, Lai Sun F & B grp always have great restaurants incl Otto e Mezzo. Roast pork was nice & crispy, dim sum is gd but not superb,$520/2 pp. Executive lunch set is $320-460!

location.address: shop 4101, Level 4 Gateway Arcade Harbour City Kowloon
formattedAddress: shop 4101, Level 4 Gateway Arcade Harbour City Kowloon

tip.text: Love the decor, modern yet full of Chinese flavour. Was looking forward to the lobster noodle which didn't disappoint me, so was the dumpling, lotus seed with berry juice, veg roll & dessert. Love it!

location.address: Shop G04, G/F, Man Yee Arcade, Man Yee Building, 68 Des Voeux Road, Central
formattedAddress: Shop G04, G/F, Man Yee Arcade, Man Yee Building, 68 Des Voeux Road, Central

tip.text: Tried this new Italian restaurant in Pacific Place. Octopus salad is good, sauce is a bit thick not the usual octopus with potato salad in olive oil, pasta is gd but sauce heavy w/butter, pizza is gd
Came here for cocktail & now try for dinner with friends, music is too loud, very casual pl, menu is a mix of yakitori, SE Asian, steak & whatever u name it. Quantity is ok but portion very small.

location.address: 23/F, California Tower, 30-36 D'Aguilar Street, Lan Kwai Fong, Central
formattedAddress: 23/F, California Tower, 30-36 D'Aguilar Street, Lan Kwai Fong, Central

tip.text: I had tried the one in Wanchai. This time, I had nicoise salad which is only ok, lack of sauce & I hv to ask for more sauce, bread comes with it. For a $120 salad, it is very expensive

location.address: Unit 008, Level LG1, Pacific Place, 88 Queensway
formattedAddress: Unit 008, Level LG1, Pacific Place, 88 Queensway

tip.text: Lovely place for happy hour (buy 1 get 1 free) with nice view of Central. Monday nite totally empty at 6:30 though. Mojito quite good though in Cannes is the best as it is made of champagne

location.address: 23/F, California Tower, 30-36 D'Aguilar Street, Lan Kwai Fong, Central
formattedAddress: 23/F, California Tower, 30-36 D'Aguilar Street, Lan Kwai Fong, Central

tip.text: Have been here before & liked the food but this time very disappointed, chicken is cold fr fridge, soup blend, sauce no taste. Will not be back!

location.address: Shop OTG16, Ocean Terminal, Harbour City, 3-27 Canton Rd
formattedAddress: Shop OTG16, Ocean Terminal, Harbour City, 3-27 Canton Rd

tip.text: Tried this newly opened Southern California style restaurant, very casual & menu very small. We ordered fish tacos, ham, onion rings, beef & chicken burger, skirt steak, seabass. Food is not too bad.

location.address: Shop 405, Level 4, Pacific Place, 88 Queens Road
formattedAddress: Shop 405, Level 4, Pacific Place, 88 Queens Road

tip.text: The portion is quite small for a $238,2-course meal no coffee/tea.My salad with salmon was just 2 fingers big, my braised chicken was good not great,the half pigeon main was mini portion like starter.
Very busy lunch venue, many varieties of dim sum dishes, good quality and affordable prices. Highly recommended!
First time here, it was Mohgul before. Nice decor unlike other Indian restaurant. Great food, we ordered samosa, veg curry, chicken tikka, naan & rice only $750 for 4 pax incl 2 glasses of wine!

First time to this ramen shop,love the soup base & choice of ingredients & garnish in particular their roast pork side dishes. The pork in my ramen is rather fat maybe I don't know which kind to order

location.address: Shop A-B, G/F, Kam Wing Commercial Bldg, 28 Minden Ave
formattedAddress: Shop A-B, G/F, Kam Wing Commercial Bldg, 28 Minden Ave (at Hart Ave)

tip.text: Traditional Cantonese cuisine but very delicious, no MSG, good service, lunch set only $75 including a soup, main & dessert! Just got Michelin starred recommendation listing!

venue.name: Sing Kee Seafood Restaurant 星記海鮮飯店

tip.text: One of the best dim sum in HK, no reservation, go before noon, high ceiling, harbour view, good service. $680 for 4 pax, what else can you ask for? Love it!

location.address: 2/F, Low Block, Hong Kong City Hall, 5 Edinburgh Pl
formattedAddress: 2/F, Low Block, Hong Kong City Hall, 5 Edinburgh Pl

tip.text: I tried this new roast duck restaurant in Central, very disappointed, soup has no taste, goose is very normal (actually not well cooked still pink) , definitely would not be back.

venue.name: Sham Tseng Chan Kee 深井陳記燒鵝

tip.text: Very busy on a sunny Sunday afternoon, full of family with kids. Only got counter seats facing the promenade, sun burning in the face. Salmon tartar, crab salad are gd, missed on calamari, $870 for 2.

location.address: Shop 103 & 104, G/F, the pulse, 28 Beach Rd
formattedAddress: Shop 103 & 104, G/F, the pulse, 28 Beach Rd

tip.text: Nobu's creamy shrimp in spicy sauce dish is my fav but today, we had assorted sushi, tako & assorted tempura, water & coffee. I was shocked the bill is $3,000! Should go to 8 1/2! Food is not worth it

Love Sai Wan Ho area with rows of restaurant by waterfront!Roast chicken was great, tomato soup is very delicious & not like fake creamy soup.Love the chef, Kenneth who comes out to greet guests,rare!

location.address: Shop GB8-10, G/F, Site B, 45 Tai Hong St
formattedAddress: Shop GB8-10, G/F, Site B, 45 Tai Hong St

tip.text: Ordered wonton & fish ball rice vermicelli, the soup base has no taste at all, wonton is nice & shrimp is crunchy but 'fish ball' is not exactly the kind (yellow color) what I expected & they too big!

venue.name: Tsim Chai Kee Noodle 沾仔記

tip.text: Typical traditional Shanghainese food, all dishes are delicious but not crazy about the eggs, love the deep fried fish!

We ordered several tapas incl calamari, octopus..taste is good though not typical Spanish. The seabass was gd though friend said a bit dried becos it was grilled butterflied. Steak & d sauce r very gd
We both had a chicken ceseare salad for $188 each, portion is good size, lots of chicken only the sauce doesn't have enough taste...maybe because the sauce is made with cottage cheese instead?

location.address: Shop 412, 4/F, Ocean Centre, Harbour City, 3-27 Canton Rd
formattedAddress: Shop 412, 4/F, Ocean Centre, Harbour City, 3-27 Canton Rd

tip.text: Have not been here for a few years, food is good,  lunch sets from $320-$480, I had pork cutlet which is yummy & generous, service is good but the crowd is noisy...don't have the 'refine' environment.

location.address: 1/F, The Peninsula Hong Kong, 9-21 Salisbury Rd
formattedAddress: 1/F, The Peninsula Hong Kong, 9-21 Salisbury Rd

tip.text: Really love this new area in Wanchai! Great environment, healthy menu, delicious salad & avocado mash toast.

location.address: Shop G40-41, G/F, Lee Tung Avenue, 200 Queen's Rd E
formattedAddress: Shop G40-41, G/F, Lee Tung Avenue, 200 Queen's Rd E

tip.text: Great varieties of Hong Kong style food- wonton noodles, congee, beef stir fried flat noodles, fried wonton & so much more. All delicious & real local authentic flavour! Long queue after 12pm.

location.address: Unit 3016-3018, 3/F, IFC Mall, 1 Harbour View St
formattedAddress: Unit 3016-3018, 3/F, IFC Mall, 1 Harbour View St

venue.name: Tasty Congee & Noodle Wantun Shop 正斗粥麵專家

tip.text: Ordered all my fav dishes: Hainese chicken rice, laksa etc. Dishes are all delicious & authentic, chow kwai teo portion was small, laksa is with thick noodle not flat, 'cheung fan' is first time, yum!

This is a private membership club, never know it exists in the past decades! I am still savouring the dishes: sweet & sour pork, tofu, shrimp with egg white, double boil soup! Delicious Cantonese food

venue.name: The Sports Club Hong Kong (五陵會)

tip.text: Our all time favourite, very casual but good food. This time, the Thai chicken is very dry, shrimp with basil is mediocre (phuket salad with shrimp is better) but their tom yum gung soup is very good!

venue.name: Shek O Thai and Chinese Restaurant

tip.text: Never have salted crepes but it is not bad, I choose the set lunch: salty crepe with bacon, egg & cheese, sweet crepe (again) with apple stew (my friend had crepe with lemon & honey) & all are yummy!
Plat du Jour is part of Swire Properties' restaurant. The burger was delicious esp I like the onions are cooked & not raw. The service was prompt as we told the waitress we have a movie to catch.
I had my fish noodle and next day my fav Singapore Fried Noodles! Great value at $58 & delicious. The noodle was fried perfectly & authentic unlike Tsui Wah style. Add $13 for cold ice milk tea! Yum!

location.address: Hong Kong Convention & Exhibition Centre, 1 Harbour Rd
formattedAddress: Hong Kong Convention & Exhibition Centre, 1 Harbour Rd

tip.text: Quite decent hotpot place but they don't have the fish skin dumpling, didn't like their fish/beef balls with cheese, strange combination, no sour plum drink, unlimited soft ice cream though...
Nice area, hotel lobby & room are small but the design & finishing is more modern. Love their heated bathroom. Food at Cafe Liang was ok esp the chow kwai teo & laksa, not too impressive of standard.

venue.name: Jing An Shangri-La (静安香格里拉大酒店)

tip.text: Start off with puntarelle salad, delicious risotto Milanese. The Cottolette is big and the tuna with carbonata is equally delicious. 3 pax for Euro 100 is great value though foccacia was not given...
Disappointed with dessert, texture feels too smooth as if it is from powder & not from fresh ingredient...taste not even as good as normal Chin restaurant...won't be back😏
Tapas dishes are tiny & a bit too salty. Paella was huge but taste not exactly those I had in Spain....wine list is expensive for such a casual restaurant. Not too impressed....
Disappointed with service, 3 of us got 2 diff menus- more expensive & cheaper(?), so confusing. We chose burger as it is cheaper ($175),other dishes $300-$450 for lunch!!! Burger was ok not juicy...

location.neighborhood: Admiralty, Central and Western District, Hong Kong

tip.text: Love eating outdoor by the pool on a beautiful sunny day. The nicoise salad is nice & portion is good but octopus salad is a bit small, not enough green & too much cucumber...they have great sandwich

location.address: 7/F, JW Marriott Hotel Hong Kong, Pacific Place, 88 Queensway
formattedAddress: 7/F, JW Marriott Hotel Hong Kong, Pacific Place, 88 Queensway

tip.text: The new seafood restaurant by Chef Gianni of Giando in Wanchai. Lots of seafood dishes, lunch sets prices different in G/F bar & upstairs restaurants. Seafood pasta was good though I prefer al dente.
Authentic Italy dishes, the restaurant & dishes,style of trattoria in Milan, simple, home-cooking yet delicious. We had pasta with puttanesca, home-made angel hair with bottarga, ox tongue,sausages😋
The place is small with a little terrace & open kitchen. The chef has put a lot of effort in using many ingredients for one dish. Food is great but not exceptional, dessert was delicious. Price high.
This is an institution, not much has changed, it didn't get modernized as the wifi goes in and out when the phone screen is closed! Service in lobby lounge has deteriorated, we have to keep calling!
Nice carrot cake, ice cappucino is ok, I like the terrace, service is good.
Always come for chicken rice here, chicken is gd portion & very tender, rice is ok but I think MO bar in HK has much better rice, sauce & soup.

formattedAddress: Level 5, Mandarin Orchard Singapore (333 Orchard Rd.)

tip.text: Recommended by our Singapore friend, love the colonal facade but interior is a bit blend. Beef redang is very tender but was not hot. Chicken was fried & small, not to die for. The veg is very salty.
Delicious and yet different from the typical laksa we had, there are lots of clams & cut up shrimps & dried tofu. No chopsticks are available as noodles are all chopped up so you could use the spoon!

Our all time favourite for Sunday family lunch with beautiful harbour view. I love the Singapore fried noodles, the best in town. Its Indian tandoori himalayan chicken with plain naan are our fav too!

location.address: Shop 101 & 201, 1-2/F, The Peak Galleria, 118 Peak Rd
formattedAddress: Shop 101 & 201, 1-2/F, The Peak Galleria, 118 Peak Rd

tip.text: Nice & bright with beautiful harbourview, draw back is the lifts are slow & pack! Scallop salad is good, steak is also delicious but not exceptional...is it because it is for wedding? Dessert is good!
Very enjoyable lunch outdoor, veal with tuna sauce, egg benedict and most refreshing & delicious is its salmon with avocado in lime & capers sauce. Cappucino has to be improved a lot though...

location.neighborhood: Admiralty, Central and Western District, Hong Kong

tip.text: We just ordered salad, quite tasty but not all healthy with fried soft shell crab in the salad, not bad for a quick meal but service need to be more alert.
The location is good, but seating in the bar is very tight. Don't see much Mercedes branding involved, there r jus some props n a car. Our mojitos are disappointing not enough palm sugar & alcohol!

location.address: Shop C-D, G/F, Entertainment Building, 30 Queen's Rd C
formattedAddress: Shop C-D, G/F, Entertainment Building, 30 Queen's Rd C

tip.text: Tried new dishes this time: $39 pigeon, lotus leaf rice, salt & pepper squid, dry noodles- all delicious esp lotus rice & pigeon. Service is efficient & food arrives promptly, will be back soon!

location.address: 2/F, The L Place, 139 Queen's Rd C
formattedAddress: 2/F, The L Place, 139 Queen's Rd C

tip.text: Lots of meat for drunken chicken in a jar, dan dan noodle is small not enough for even one person, good dumplings & cabbage in soy milk. Will be back soon!

location.address: 2/F, The L Place, 139 Queen's Rd C
formattedAddress: 2/F, The L Place, 139 Queen's Rd C

tip.text: The best authentic pizza in HK, great dough, wooden oven,lots of topping choices (missing artichokes)! Nice appetizer esp octopus salad & oven baked calamari. Surprise dessert w/ nutella & marshmellow

Every dish is chilli & some with pepper corn which numbs your lips but the dishes are not so unbearable at all. We had pork, chicken, eggplant, fish, all delicious but alot of oil, guess it is typical
First time since Wanya moved from Central to L Place, nice location, good simple decor not as noisy as before. Still have 14 set lunches which change regularly, prices approx $218.

location.address: 1/F, The L Place, 139 Queen's Rd C
formattedAddress: 1/F, The L Place, 139 Queen's Rd C

tip.text: Good quality dim sum, all freshly made once order is placed, good value for money just wish they have more branches in Central...no reservation better go around noon or after 2pm.

location.address: G/F, Fu Fai Commercial Centre, 27 Hillier St
formattedAddress: G/F, Fu Fai Commercial Centre, 27 Hillier St

contact.facebookName: 聚點坊點心專門店 Dim Sum Square

tip.text: Food is always good though it is specialising on fish. The fish BLT sandwich is gigantic, very filling, fries are delicious. Just note free 2 hr parking is for $800 bill, ours: $567 & hv to pay $160!

location.address: 7/F, JW Marriott Hotel Hong Kong, Pacific Place, 88 Queensway
formattedAddress: 7/F, JW Marriott Hotel Hong Kong, Pacific Place, 88 Queensway

tip.text: Good authentic taste of pho, $61 lunch set includes my favourite chicken pho, choice of side dish and Vietnamese drink under $25. Great value for money, after renovation, much cleaner and nicer.

venue.name: Phõ Tài 越南牛肉粉專門店

tip.text: Great happy hour, $5 for first drink fr 5-7pm then $45 per drink thereafter. Good portion of snacks for fries and calamari! Good vibes!
Great lunch location with lots of lunch sets at good price. Scallop with organic rice is delicious, juicy and tasty but the beetroot salad is too chunky and not tasty.

location.neighborhood: Central, Central and Western District, Hong Kong

tip.text: Famous for its soup noodles, my favourite is wonton flat rice noodles and congee. They have lots of set lunch choices including fry noodles and rice.
Food is good, not exceptional, place is very tight esp in the private dining room, spot light shines straight into my eyes, annoying though manager dimmed it. Expensive for what it is at $1k each.
Good quality and portion on the dishes except the noodle which is quite small. The beef dishes is chunky with meat, good value. Will return soon!

location.address: 2/F, The L Place, 139 Queen's Rd C
formattedAddress: 2/F, The L Place, 139 Queen's Rd C

tip.text: New lunch menu, still yummy tapas, good value for money, great space. Love the croquette and chorizo!
New lunch tapas menu, delicious, good value and enough choices with chorizo, pasta, calamari, beef etc ,missed the anchovy on toast though. Could share with friends, will return soon!
Newly opened for a few months, sushi is fresh, lunch set is good price for money especially chicken teriyaki which has a sumptuous portion.
Food is genuine, tasty but fish sauce with chili was very salty, it makes us extremely thirsty after meal. Place is small and price is expensive for its location and place. A lunch for 2 was $670!
Pizza is the best we had in Italy as the flour used is different, friita calamari & cozze (mussels) are delicious! Best dinner we had in Formia!
Best restaurant recommended by our Roman friend, book early, sit in terrace. Famous for matriciana pasta, comes in a pan!
Best pizza and freshest seafood you could find in Gaeta near Formia. Owners are 2nd generation, opened for 60 years. We don't even have to order, he just bring us the best. 6 pax for Euro90!
Milanese cottolette (veal) is the best, can't leave without having this. Bombana is famous for his risotto, ruffle, pasta- everything as he picks best & fresh ingredients. 8 1/2 Macau just opened!
Good quesadilla! Burritos is delicious too but big for one person, share so you could try other dishes
Disappointing on drinks (lycee lemongrass & lemongrass has no taste), service, price is expensive, food portion is small, no soup comes with Hainese Chicken Rice & Redang chicken is not spicy enough.

location.address: 5/F., The L Place, 139 Queen's Rd C
formattedAddress: 5/F., The L Place, 139 Queen's Rd C

tip.text: Good lunch set, fish curry & pork belly were delicious, non-stop refill for ice chai tea. Only thing is air condition is freezing and blowing directly, bring a fur!

Have to go early to get a seat/table, no reservation & limit to 1.5 hr for dining which is a drag. Love the soft tacos & cocktail. Try the Queso fundido which is melted cheese, beans served in 3 tacos
Definitely the best & not the typical yakitori place, great food! Have to try the ox tongue, fried fish, minced chicken skewer, beef with mustard sauce, all good! Have to return soon!
Great varieties of breakfast at affordable prices, generous portion just like its lunch set.
Have not been back since its renovation from Aqua's Chin restaurant. Nice spacious interior and very good tapas lunch set, quality and portion is good size, will definitely come back.
Best Hainanese Chicken Rice together with Cafe Causette in sister hotel, Mandarin Oriental. Great environment, service & location, it is a hip place to be seen.

location.address: G/F, The Landmark Mandarin Oriental Hotel, 15 Queen’s Rd C
formattedAddress: G/F, The Landmark Mandarin Oriental Hotel, 15 Queen’s Rd C

contact.facebookName: MO Bar at The Landmark Mandarin Oriental, Hong Kong

tip.text: Xiao long bao is quite good, dan dan noodle's soup is nice & spicy but too much soup while traditionally have ground pork and much less soup but overall it is good food

location.address: Shop E01-E06, Lab Concept, 1/F, Queensway Plaza, 93 Queensway
formattedAddress: Shop E01-E06, Lab Concept, 1/F, Queensway Plaza, 93 Queensway

venue.name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao 翡翠拉麵小籠包 (翡翠拉麵小籠包)

tip.text: Never been to this private room/bar, beef cheek is very tender, though I don't eat lamb, this one is very delicious and no wild taste.
Nice cosy interior, interesting smoky aubergine canapes but the pasta & risotto has too much butter which is not typical Italian. Not sure if the chef has to adapt to local Chinese taste or not.
Good efficient service, the ramen is not bad but I have better ones. The gyoza is nice but unusual as they put lots of ginger & green onion on top.
Limited menu, mediocre food, completely bad decor, fine dining but door to street opens, noisy, wrong ambience & music,only good thing is staff is OK

location.address: Shop 2, G/F, The Centrium, 60 Wyndham Street
formattedAddress: Shop 2, G/F, The Centrium, 60 Wyndham Street

venue.name: Old Bazaar Kitchen 老巴剎廚房

tip.text: Very impressive with the special catered dinner, creative & delicious!
Surprisingly delicious French cuisine which is nice & light unlike typical heavy dishes, it has some Japanese touch & makes it unique
Nice deco, more open space , delicous short rib & I heard tuna is very good

location.neighborhood: Admiralty, Central and Western District, Hong Kong

tip.text: A typical bar/restaurant quality of food, if you want enchiladas, burritos, tacos, guacamole, you have them all. Nothing to die for but good for a quench of Tex Mex food.
